sql:
SELECT f.feature_name
FROM features f
JOIN nodes n ON f.feature_id = n.feature_id
WHERE n.class = 'Class_1' AND f.feature_importance > (
    SELECT AVG(feature_importance) FROM features
);

external_knowledge:
Frequent access is defined as having more than 10 entries in the access logs;
Data scientists are users with the 'data scientist' role;
Predictions are assumed to be operations with an 'access_type' of 'predict'.

sql:
SELECT node_description 
FROM nodes 
WHERE node_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
Node types 'internal' and 'leaf' are typically used in decision trees; Internal nodes represent decisions or tests, while leaf nodes represent the predicted class labels or outcomes.; 
The threshold value is used to determine the decision or test at each internal node; 
Features are the input variables or attributes used to make predictions in a decision tree.
